          "That is where the Avana spoke fits in. It is being designed as a dedicated market for LP backed borrowing, particularly around AMM positions such as Uniswap concentrated liquidity. Instead of forcing those positions into a generic lending framework, the idea is to support them through a structure that recognizes how they actually behave. The spoke can define how collateral is evaluated, how borrowing power is assigned, and how risk is handled at the level of the position itself, while the hub continues to provide the shared liquidity that makes borrowing possible in the first place.",
          "This distinction becomes especially important with Uniswap LP positions because they are not simple fungible tokens with fixed properties. A concentrated liquidity position is a structured market position. Its value depends on the current price of the underlying assets, the amount of liquidity provided, the selected price range, and the fees accrued over time. It can be active and earning, or it can move out of range and behave very differently. That means a lending protocol cannot safely treat it like a static balance. It has to understand the composition of the position in real time and evaluate what that position is worth not just notionally, but as collateral under changing market conditions.",
