          "Once that foundation exists, the borrowing flow becomes conceptually simple even if the underlying mechanics are complex. A user supplies a supported Uniswap LP position as collateral through the Avana spoke. The position remains active in the AMM and continues to earn trading fees. The spoke evaluates the collateral, applies the relevant risk logic, and allows the user to borrow supported assets by drawing on shared liquidity from the hub. From the user’s point of view, the system is meant to feel coherent: one position remains productive in the market while also becoming a source of credit.",
          "That is one of the key advantages of the design. Collateralizing the position does not mean turning it off. The liquidity can stay deployed, market exposure can remain intact, and fees can continue to accrue throughout the life of the loan. In that sense, LP backed borrowing is not just about leverage. It is about making productive capital more flexible. A position that previously had to be unwound in order to access liquidity can instead remain active while supporting credit at the same time.",
